id: pm-afl9
title: Generate full historical CHANGELOG.md through pm-changelog
description: "Use the latest npm pm-changelog package to generate and validate the main CHANGELOG.md as full historical release/change history for pm-cli, covering all pm tracker items at least once where package functionality allows. If pm-changelog lacks required capability, document the defect upstream in unbraind/pm-changelog and fix it there rather than adding a custom generator in pm-cli."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: changelog,ci,packages,release,sdk
created_at: "2026-05-24T15:18:30.941Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T16:11:01.712Z"
author: codex-changelog-full-history
parent: pm-59gj
resolution: "Installed and verified pm-changelog@2026.5.24-14, switched pm-cli changelog scripts to package-owned full-history generation, regenerated CHANGELOG.md, updated release/CI contracts, and incorporated bot-review feedback through upstream pm-changelog issue #11."
expected_result: "CHANGELOG.md is generated by pm-changelog, covers historical released changes and Unreleased tracker items, and CI checks fail when the generated file is stale."
actual_result: "pm-changelog generated 808 closed item entries across git-tag release windows and Unreleased coverage; package doctor, contracts, changelog check, focused tests, build, release gates, Sentry, telemetry health checks, and upstream pm-changelog@2026.5.24-14 release verification passed."
comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-24T15:18:41.674Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Duplicate check: ran pm context, pm search, pm list-open, pm list-in-progress, and GitHub issue snapshots. Reusing parent pm-59gj; prior exact item pm-5baq is closed and only verified the latest v2026.5.24 release section with 39 items, while this task covers the stronger full-history/800+ item requirement."
  "2026-05-24T15:23:16.689Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Upstream package gap found: pm-changelog@2026.5.24-11 can generate 807 full-history items but only as one current-version section or tracker release metadata groups; it cannot derive actual git release tag windows. Filed unbraind/pm-changelog#10 and moving the fix upstream."
  "2026-05-24T15:44:01.055Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Upstream fix published: pm-changelog@2026.5.24-13 includes --all-release-tags full git-tag history generation, zero-padded calendar tag matching, and CI tag checkout fixes. npm latest and GitHub release v2026.05.24-13 verified."
  "2026-05-24T15:54:40.927Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Evidence: pm-changelog@2026.5.24-13 is installed as the project extension, exposes changelog generate --all-release-tags and --release-tag-pattern through runtime contracts, and generated CHANGELOG.md via pnpm changelog:pm with 807 closed pm items plus Unreleased coverage. Verification passed: pnpm changelog:pm:check, focused release-readiness/release-automation tests, pnpm build, pm package doctor, pm contracts, release gates with required telemetry/Sentry, and pm health telemetry probe."
  "2026-05-24T16:10:59.674Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Follow-up review evidence: Gemini feedback on pm-cli#62 identified a pm-changelog package-side performance issue. Filed unbraind/pm-changelog#11, fixed it upstream, released pm-changelog@2026.5.24-14 through the Daily Release workflow, verified npm latest and GitHub release v2026.05.24-14, and reinstalled that latest package in this repo."
